DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(91)90056-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387891900562
AB  - In order to maximize the revenue productivity of their intangible assets, affiliates of MNEs are more likely to pursue non-price rivalry than their host country counterparts. The choice of rivalry is expected to get reflected on different aspects of firms' conduct and performance. Comparing the behaviour of two groups of firms in 49 Indian industries this paper finds, in tune with the predictions, that MNE affiliates operate at relatively larger scales, enjoy higher profit margins, are more vertically integrated and fund flush witm more skilled personnel. For advertising and R & D inputs they benefit also from the global expenditures of their associates.
